cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the communication technologies used in public safety networks, which involves network infrastructure, wireless communication, and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the security aspects of the communication systems, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the simulation and experimental studies of the communication systems, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper reviews emerging technologies, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
